<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-01-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-01-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="349" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d349">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Lord Lyons</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-01-03"><hi rend="italic">January</hi> 3, 1863.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">My Lord</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 31st ultimo, relative to the sale of the
                            prize steamer Bermuda, and to state, in reply, that a copy of it has
                            been sent to the Secretary of the Navy for. his information.</p>
                        <p>I avail myself of this opportunity to renew to your lordship the
                            assurance of my highest consideration.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>Right Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">Lord Lyons</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>